Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

There are no regular commercial options available to return to the UK from Maldives following decisions taken by commercial airlines.
However, we understand Qatar Airways intends to operate a flight from Male’ to Doha on 21 April, with onward connections to the UK available from Doha. Please contact the Qatar Airways airline office on 3334777 for further information. Speak to your airline or travel company if you are still in Maldives.
What to do
If you cannot leave the Maldives at this time, you should:
Follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus
Find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs. If your accommodation is not available and you are being asked to leave, please contact us for consular assistance by calling +94 11 5390639 or Direct Message @UKinMaldives on Twitter
Keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well
Continue to follow our travel advice
The British High Commission Male’ is issuing regular updates on Twitter with the latest available information for British nationals wishing to leave Maldives
Future travel options
The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Maldivians authorities and other government to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible. This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission on Twitter.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission on +94 11 5390639.
The High Commission cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
